    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "881bc9fc_dda3a1dc",
        "filename": "src/gpu/GrBlockAllocator.h",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 55,
      "author": {
        "id": 5085
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-01-14T18:23:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This creation pattern means that there\u0027s always one additional heap allocation to use GrBlockAllocator. It doesn\u0027t allow a user to make a GrBlockAllocator and std::aligned_storage in the user\u0027s memory. I wonder if that\u0027s something we will want? SkArenaAlloc lets you do this.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 52,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 55,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "2d370bd6b77db8ec8e383466cdfa28ab1c8225d7",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "dfa1cfd8_493785b5",
        "filename": "src/gpu/GrBlockAllocator.h",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 55,
      "author": {
        "id": 8341
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-01-15T16:10:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Subclasses use the protected static Prealloc function to make a single heap allocation for themselves, the GrBlockAllocator, and the first head block. With some care, a subclass could set it up instead to have the head block point to their own aligned storage / user memory. I will probably add something like that for handling GrAllocator, but in the short term, this Make() is only used when creating a GrBlockAllocator directly and Gr[Op]MemoryPool still only require one allocation when making them.",
      "parentUuid": "881bc9fc_dda3a1dc",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 52,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 55,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "2d370bd6b77db8ec8e383466cdfa28ab1c8225d7",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
